<subSubSection id="FE4250C4242793EAA1A8EB2EC905E871" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FCA759132E1A4DBEBE4CA259099C07BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87DEE3722001B75DE73940A54AA42CFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">
Habitus: Fig. 
<figureCitation id="41D3FB2EF6BBB8D8189772F07DBE6625" captionStartId="F7786916" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">1</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="27EBE6E2EF96801C624377D019AC963B" captionStartId="F7786926" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">f</figureCitation>
. Maxillary palpus: Fig. 
<figureCitation id="833468B34C030587F6DD75FD514D1094" captionStartId="F7787287" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">3</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="5A7FC65A70AA66F8D0F5D32301C4E805" captionStartId="F7787297" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">f</figureCitation>
. Pronotum: Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7D12622FF63A92EB76AF755BC8AC41B3" captionStartId="F7787234" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">4</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="9A04E295016CAB52557911E426858D59" captionStartId="F7787242" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">d</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D6661919F15FE3508ABABF12CC71F33" pageId="0" pageNumber="84104">Body length = 11.7 mm. Dorsal surface black. Similar to the nominal-typical subspecies, but different in the pronotum being only sparsely punctate between basal foveae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
